affliction.&quot;; THE JACKET WEARS WELL; Cal footballcoach Bruce Snyder knows the beige jacket he's wearing on game days is ugly.But what can he do? The Bears are 4-0, and it's his lucky jacket. &quot;My wife(Linda) hates it, and I don't like it,&quot; Snyder said. &quot;It's older than the guysI'm coaching.&quot;; ' We were a team, but we were not a family . . . and theBraves were both. We came to the park, we worked, and then we went ourseparate ways. We were too many individuals and not enough of a group. '--Brett Butler of the Dodgers  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Information for this column was compiled from Mercury News wire services byColin Seymour. Staff writers John Akers and Mark Gonzales contributed.  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911008  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  399  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday, October 8, 199100282078,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>